2003-03-16 16:05 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/inet.c
    + Added InetStatus() function to get the status of a socket. Currently used
      to know if a socket is active (0) or closed (-1): TODO more status
    ! Put HB_STACK_LOCK/UNLOCK and HB_TEST_CANCEL_ENABLE_ASYN/ DISABLE in
      the right places. Now asynchronous killing of a thread waiting on a socket is
      working ( use KillThread()/jointhread )

  * source/rtl/trpc.prg
    ! Using cleaner cleanup of accepting tread, closing their sockets instead of killing
      them.

2003-03-16 13:56 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/thread.c
    + added internal function hb_getCurrentStackNoError() to find a stack
      or return null if stack were not present. hb_getCurrentStack() was
      primarily meant to be used by HB_VM_STACK macro and thus rose an
      error when called with an invalid th_id.

  * source/rtl/trpc.prg
  * source/rtl/trpccli.prg
    ! Using KillThraed() /JoinThread() combination instead of StopThread()
    ! Error in cyclic function decoding corrected.

2003-03-16 08:27 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * test/rpcclient.prg
    ! Removed InetInit() (is done by trpc).

  ! source/vm/inet.c
    ! Fixed UDP protocol recv.

2003-03-16 07:15 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * tests/mtcomplex.prg
    ! StopThread() is not anymore suitable to kill the monitor thread:
      changed to KillThread()

2003-03-16 06:53 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * vm/codebloc.c
  * vm/garbage.c
  * vm/hvm.c
    ! Important fixes made to various part of the code to avoid potential
      segfaults and deadlocks. The stack locking range has been increased,
      so GC can't take over i.e. returning functions or exiting codeblocks.

  * vm/thread.c
    ! Released stack before entering PRG mutex wait. That could cause deadlocks
      with fence idle actived.

  * rtl/console.c
    ! changed the order of stack/ hb_outputMutex locks

  * rtl/idle.c
    ! removed stack unlocking/locking that were guarding the GC collection. Now
      it is done in GC.

  + doc/xhbt_internals.txt
    + Added documentation on the internal programming of hb threads.

