2003-03-07 14:30 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/rdd/dbfntx/dbfntx1.c
  * source/rtl/fstemp.c
    ! In linux, tmpname() issues a warining at link time. Usage of mkstemp()
      is FORCED instead (is also a MUCH MORE safe function, avoiding races
      and guess-the-temp-name vunlerability attacks).
      I am using it only on LINUX, but other UNIXes programmers might want
      to extend it's usage also on their systems.
      Also, that warning prevented scrips from detecting that link has
      been completed sucessfully.


