2003-02-23 21:15 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/rtl/hbcompress.c
    - Removed adler32() checksum function, because...

  + source/rtl/hbchecksum.c
    + moved here adler32() function, with a new front end called
      HB_CHECKSUM( cStr ) -> nCheckSum32bit

  * source/rtl/trpc.prg
  * source/rtl/trpccli.prg
    + Added support for cyclic remote procedure call; now RPC can be
      called defining a for/next cluse or a foreach clause. The loop
      will be done in the server (there is no need to fill the network
      with operations: one request, one summary reply or all replies).

  * tests/rpcclient.prg
    + Added a test of foreach RPC call

  + source/rtl/hbhextonum.c
    + Added functions
      HB_HexToNum( cHexString )--> nNum
      HB_NumToHex( nNum ) --> cHexString

  * include/Makefile
  + include/hbnxs.h
  * source/rtl/Makefile
  + source/rtl/hbcrypt.c
    + Added HB_Crypt() and HB_Decrypt() functions. At the moment, this two
      functions allows only simmetric encryption with NXS algorithm, an
      algorithm provided by me; but the idea here is that HB_Crypt/HB_Decrypt
      SHOULD be frontend for all encription methods we may want to add.

      Currently:
         HB_Crypt( cData, cKey ) --> cCipher
         HB_Decrypt( cCipher, cKey ) --> cData
      In the future, there will be also space for cipher method.

  + tests/crypt.prg
    + test for crypt functions.


2003-02-22 20:40 UTC-0300 Marcelo Lombardo <lombardo@uol.com.br>
