    ! Fixed bug importing from txt: if the last txt line does not ends with CRLF it
      is not ignored anymore.
    ! Tab idents removed

2003-02-22 09:14 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    * Enahnced HB_QSelf() to recive optional paramater <nLevel> much like ProcName().



2003-02-22 06:53 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/arrays.c
    ! Locked all arrays operations

  * source/vm/fm.c
    ! hb_allocMutex was not initialized if statistics were off.

  * source/vm/garbage.c
    * minor style fixes

  * source/vm/thread.c
    * Added function KillAllThreads() to terminate all waiting
      threads from inside the .prg program (i.e. a error
      detection routine).

  * tests/mtcomplex.prg
    + Added a KillAllThreads() test
    * Visual upgrade

  * config/gcc.cf
    + ADDED -DHB_OS_LINUX to better identify linux specific extensions
    - REMOVED "-g" (debug) switch from default compilation. You will have
      to add it to CUSR to have this in.

  * include/hbsetup.h
    + Added #ifdef HB_OS_LINUX --> #define HB_OS_UNIX

  * include/hbstack.h
  * include/thread.h
    % Now thread is ALWAYS included if stack is included. If thread support
      is disabled, HB_MUTEX_LOCK() and HB_MUTEX_UNLOCK() are defined void,
      so there is no need to guard all calls to them in other files with
      #ifdef thread support.
    % Under linux, using system specific implementations of reentrant mutex.
      Other systems will still need the LightWeight Reentrant Mutexes,
      unless we implement specific reentrant pthread implementation for them
      (that is non-startard posix). I know both BSD and Darwin has reentrant
      mutexes.


