2003-02-20 02:35 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! Under windows, instead of using suspended creation of threads,
      using a blocking mutex at the beginning to make sure all
      creation rights are fulfilled. Also, the thread handle is not
      taken by the created thread (but taken in the creator) because
      there is the need of specific rights to open a thread handle
      under windows 2000/xp

2003-02-20 01:30 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/garbage.c
    ! now a second thread can't run GC exactly after another one
      has just finished GC

2003-02-19 21:15 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * samples/sitesvr/sitesvr.prg
    ! Removed some test code and added some mutexes for increased
      stability.

  * source/rtl/trpc.prg
    + Added callbacs in the server code, so final application can
      monitor connection(s) status.
    % Now thread servicing client connections is encapsulated in his
      own class
    * Code for encription has been put in place; an encription back
      end will be soon added

  * source/rtl/trpccli.prg
    ! minor fixes

  * source/vm/fm.c
  * source/vm/thread.c
    ! malloc can be intrinsically thread unsafe (depending on os,
      but generally it is). For this reason, a global
      hb_allocMutex has been added on fm.c: this mutex is used to
      lock out sections in fm.c, but also to regulate all malloc(),
      realloc() and free() calls in MT programs. Thread.c is the
      first file revised, in the next hours I will lock all malloc
      calls, or translate them in hb_x...() calls.

  * tests/rpcclient.prg
    * Minor stylistic fixes

  * tests/rpcserver.prg
    + Implementation of the new callbacks


2003-02-19 17:50 UTC+0100 Ian Anderson <ianderson@procon-online.de>
  * make_b32.bat
    ! added -l flag to Make command to fix problem with long command
    lines

2003-02-19 17:30 UTC+0100 Ian Anderson <ianderson@procon-online.de>
  * source/common/hbtrace.c
    ! HB_TRACELEVEL() now works as documented in tracing.txt
    hb_tracelevel() was setting the wrong variable for the trace
    level, and hb_tr_trace() was not testing correctly to see if the
    trace should be displayed at the current level setting

2003-02-19 13:14 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    % Using now HB_VM_STACK optimization (reading stack only once
      per function) when threads are enabled

2003-02-19 11:50 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/classes.c
  * source/vm/thread.c
  * include/hbstack.h
    ! Current selected method was stored in a static module variable.
      This practice was not thread safe, and I have moved the s_pMethod
      variable into the stack.
      THIS REQUIRE MAKE CLEAN IN ORDER TO WORK, or (probably) any
      application using classes could crash.


2003-02-19 11:15 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added LISP like array direct call to HB_ExecFromArray:
      HB_ExecFromArray( aArray )
      Where aArray must have one of the following formats:
      aArray := { @Func(), param1 .. paramN }
      aArray := { "FunctionName", param1 .. paramN }
      aArray := { oObject, "MethodName", param1 .. paramN }
      aArray := { oObject, nMethodID, param1 .. paramN }
      NOTE: HB_ExecFromArray() Returns the data returned by
      the called function or method.

  * tests/exec.prg
    + test to demonstrate this new features

2003-02-19 03:03 UTC+0100 Francesco Saverio Giudice <info@fsgiudice.com>
  * include/hbclass.ch
    * fixed AddClsMethod name typo
    + added automatic constructor call with parameters throught Class Name
      oMyClass := TClass( "par1", par2, ... )
      is the same of
      oMyClass := TClass():New( "par1", par2, ... )
    + added Class Methods definition, but not finished
    + added CONSTRUCTOR / DESTRUCTOR definitions
    + added OVERRIDE optional parameter to METHOD syntax, only as an explicit word
      to remember that a method will be overrided in this class
    + added DYNAMIC parameter like Delphi syntax. Equivalent to VIRTUAL parameter.
  * source/rtl/tclass.prg
    + ConstructorCall() method added
      this automatically calls the object constructor if there are parameters passed
  + tests/clsctor.prg
    + test to demonstrate the new call syntax

  -------------------------------
  NOTE: Actually the only real change is the Class Name call with parameters
        others are little modifications that don't change actual programs.
        To use above new sintax you have to make a clean build.


2003-02-18 18:06 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron@ronpinkas.com>
  * source/compiler/harbour.sly
    ! Fixed imporoper generation of HB_ResetTry() portion of TRY syntax.

2003-02-19 00:55 UTC+0100 Giancarlo Niccolai <gian@niccolai.ws>
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    + Added function HB_ExecFromArray with the following syntax:
      HB_ExecFromArray( @Func(), aArray )
      HB_ExecFromArray( "FunctionName", aArray )
      HB_ExecFromArray( oObject, "MethodName", aArray )
      HB_ExecFromArray( oObject, nMethodID, aArray )
      The aArray elements are passed into the paramter list of the target
      function or methods.
      TODO --> return of the called function must be returened by this
      function, and also by HB_Exec function. Can someone lend me a
      hand here?

  * tests/exec.prg
    + test to demonstrate this feature


